Prepare barbecue (medium-high heat). Mix cantaloupe, onion, cilantro, 2 teaspoons oil, lime juice and jalape√±o chili in small bowl. Season salsa to taste with salt and pepper. Let stand 15 minutes. Meanwhile, brush tuna steaks on both sides with remaining 2 teaspoons olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Grill tuna until just opaque in center, about 3 minutes per side. Transfer tuna to plates. Spoon salsa alongside and serve.